 The Winter Olympic and Paralympic Village of Beijing 2022 will provide full-time service for athletes, coaches and officials during the Games, 53 days in total, in the three competition zones of Beijing, Yanqing and Zhangjiakou respectively. The Village will start trial operation for the Olympics on January 23, officially open on January 27, and be closed on February 23. It will then launch its trial operation for the Paralympics on February 23, open on February 25, and be closed on March 16, according to the Beijing Major Projects Construction Headquarters Office. The construction of the Olympic and Paralympic Village in the Beijing competition zone started on September 27, 2018 and was completed on June 26, 2021. Produced by Xinhua Global Service